say she had planted 50,000 trees,=E2=80=9D and who simultaneously signed a =
contract with Apogee Pacific that =E2=80=9Cwould pay Loaiza $55,000 per mon=
th for =E2=80=98marketing and branding services=E2=80=99 and would =E2=80=
=98last for as long as=E2=80=99 she worked with Aspiration.=E2=80=9D Paying=
 $55,000 for $50,000 of revenue=C2=A0<em>sounds=C2=A0</em>like a bad invest=
ment, but if it gets you to a $2 billion initial public offering it could b=
