the latest on that</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Microso=
ft Corp. and Apple Inc. dropped plans to take board roles at OpenAI in a su=
rprise decision that underscores growing regulatory scrutiny of Big Tech=E2=
=80=99s influence over artificial intelligence.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Microsoft, which invested $13 billion in the ChatGPT creator, will wit=
hdraw from its observer role on the board, the company said in a letter to =
OpenAI on Tuesday, which was seen by Bloomberg News. Apple was due to take =
up a similar role, but an OpenAI spokesperson said the startup won=E2=80=99=
t have board observers after Microsoft=E2=80=99s departure.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Regulators in the US and Europe had expressed concerns abo=
ut Microsoft=E2=80=99s sway over OpenAI, applying pressure on one of the wo=
rld=E2=80=99s most valuable companies to show that it=E2=80=99s keeping the=
 relationship at arm=E2=80=99s length. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">OpenAI said that moving forward, the company will host regular stakeh=
older meetings with partners and investors, including Thrive Capital and Kh=
osla Ventures, =E2=80=9Cto share progress on our mission and ensure stronge=
r collaboration across safety and security.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Microsoft won=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>observe the board m=
eetings</em>, it will just <em>go to the regular stakeholder meetings</em>,=
 completely different thing, no antitrust problem here!</p><table class=3D"=
header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
